# Execution Discipline

- Do not choose a temporary, partial, or "fast" fix when the user expects the correct fix.
- If a proper fix requires changes across contracts, migrations, generated data, backend logic, or UI, do the proper fix.
- Do not ship compatibility band-aids in place of restoring the source-of-truth contract unless the user explicitly asks for a temporary workaround.
- When a regression is caused by a broken contract, fix the contract at the correct layer first.
- If there is any doubt between "quick patch" and "right fix", choose the right fix.
